"source":"rec9RWmgEFZd3mQeS","target":"receEjvf5hXhkgVuZ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9RWmgEFZd3mQeS","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9RWmgEFZd3mQeS","target":"recGUuZfUbylFAytG","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec9bScBpR9cXupa4","ref":"Ezek.27.1","text":"The word of the LORD came again unto me, saying,","year":-588},{"id":"reckbKeJsm3LsFBnU","ref":"Ezek.27.2","text":"Now, thou son of man, take up a lamentation for Tyrus;","year":-588},{"id":"recuOABhqlNWIEF9Y","ref":"Ezek.27.3","text":"And say unto Tyrus, O thou that art situate at the entry of the sea, which art a merchant of the people for many isles, Thus saith the Lord GOD; O Tyrus, thou hast said, I am of perfect beauty.","year":-588},{"id":"recO6fv1XDvzfBfM5","ref":"Ezek.27.4","text":"Thy borders are in the midst of the seas, thy builders have perfected thy beauty.","year":-588},{"id":"recIBcSj7gJ1Adj6U","ref":"Ezek.27.5","text":"They have made all thy ship boards of fir trees of Senir: they have taken cedars from Lebanon to make masts for thee.","year":-588},{"id":"recgOuZtGSYWj07yw","ref":"Ezek.27.6","text":"Of the oaks of Bashan have they made thine oars; the company of the Ashurites have made thy benches of ivory, brought out of the isles of Chittim.","year":-588},{"id":"reckDxnUjaUeqe7Me","ref":"Ezek.27.7","text":"Fine linen with broidered work from Egypt was that which thou spreadest forth to be thy sail; blue and purple from the isles of Elishah was that which covered thee.","year":-588},{"id":"recwn6YDbz1U5Kloz","ref":"Ezek.27.8","text":"The inhabitants of Zidon and Arvad were thy mariners: thy wise men, O Tyrus, that were in thee, were thy pilots.","year":-588}]}
